	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65022469"><p><div class="quote"><p>I am all for specificity, but in the end simplicity in communication structure is far superior. List format is much cleaner than the verbosity 99% of the time.</p></div><p>Specificity and simplicity are mutually exclusive. Generalising creates simplicity. The problem is the entire legal profession exists purely as an exercise of determining edge cases (along with a few stupidly obvious lawsuits).</p><p>As for list format, most contracts are already numbered paragraphs. The act of being a list doesn't make something simple.</p></div>
	</div>

