		<div id="comment_body_65022629"><p>No it doesn't as IT and programming no matter how specific the specs a customer gives me, if I am in any doubt I will clarify. And even after doing my best at implementing what I believe the customer wants it will go through user acceptance testing to be certain and there are inevitably differences of opinion. The spec is irrelevant at that point apart from who pays for the changes the product has to be what the customer wanted.</p><p>In the end its about balance, spending years developing a spec starts to get dim<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65022629">

</div>
